# Trionic loader artifacts are integrity-checked by SHA-256 in
# firmware/trionic/loaders.py against pinned values in manifest.json. Line
# ending normalization (e.g. Windows core.autocrlf) silently changes their
# bytes and breaks that check, so they must never be text-converted on
# checkout — even the .s19 file, despite being ASCII, is a byte-exact pinned
# artifact, not source text.
firmware/trionic/loaders/*.s19 -text
firmware/trionic/loaders/*.bin -text binary
